bug.summary: The contents of Transfer learning tutorial and its github source are not the same.
bug.description:
<denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/alpha/tutorials/images/transfer_learning>https://www.tensorflow.org/alpha/tutorials/images/transfer_learning</denchmark-link>
This is the tutorial for transfer learning for tensorflow 2.0 but if you click on run on colab or view source on github buttons, then the contents are not the same (colab link : <denchmark-link:https://colab.research.google.com/github/tensorflow/docs/blob/master/site/en/tutorials/images/transfer_learning.ipynb>https://colab.research.google.com/github/tensorflow/docs/blob/master/site/en/tutorials/images/transfer_learning.ipynb</denchmark-link>

comments.comment:
Thanks. These links have been fixed upstream: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/docs/blob/master/site/en/r2/tutorials/images/transfer_learning.ipynb>https://github.com/tensorflow/docs/blob/master/site/en/r2/tutorials/images/transfer_learning.ipynb</denchmark-link>
And will be reflected on the website when the next site publish happens. If you're learning, I'd go with the alpha/r2 docs (though some of them are still in alpha condition)
